N:task-planning
D:Turn vague features, bugs, roadmap items, or playtest findings into execution-ready tasks, sprint...
G:task-planning backlog-grooming sprint-planning roadmap-slicing feature-breakdown
U[4]:
  Break features, bug clusters, roadmap items, or ideas into actionable work
  Groom a backlog before sprint or milestone planning
  Turn scattered notes, PRDs, specs, or playtest findings into execution slices
  Separate discovery from implementation when work is not ready
X[3]:
  sizing-only or story-point requests -> task-estimation
  daily cadence or blocker roundups -> standup-meeting
  completed-work reflection -> sprint-retrospective
S[4]{n,action}:
  1,Identify the planning horizon
  2,Define the planning packet
  3,Break work into execution-ready slices
  4,Surface sequencing blockers and recommended next move
R[5]:
  planning horizon labeled
  dependencies and missing inputs visible
  discovery separated from implementation when uncertainty is material
  every slice has acceptance criteria or a not-ready reason
  output ends with a recommended next move
